shapes:IntervalUsageRequestTemplateShape
    a sh:NodeShape ;
    sh:targetClass ids:IntervalUsageRequest ;
    sh:node shapes:HasProviderOrConsumerNodeShape ;
    sh:property shapes:IntervalUsageRequestTemplate-permissionPropertyShape ;
    sh:message "<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/International-Data-Spaces-Association/InformationModel/master/examples/contract-and-usage-policy/templates/TimeRestrictedUsageTemplates/IntervalUsageRequestTemplateShape.ttl> (IntervalUsageRequestTemplateShape): In a _:IntervalUsageRequest a) the ids:provider property must point to one participant or b) the ids:consumer property must point to one participant or c) the ids:provider and the ids:consumer must point to one participant. This can in any case be a) an IRI or b) an ids:Participant. The ids:permission property must point to at exactly one ids:Permission. In the ids:Permission the ids:target and ids:action properties and at least one of (ids:assigner or ids:assignee) pointing to a participant have to be specified. There must be two ids:constraint properties pointing to an ids:Constraint each. Within one ids:Constrint the ids:leftOperand must point to idsc:POLICY_EVALUATION_TIME, the ids:operator must point to idsc:AFTER and the ids:rightOperand must specify the start timestamp of the interval as xsd:dateTimeStamp. Within the other ids:Constraint the ids:leftOperand must point to idsc:POLICY_EVALUATION_TIME, the ids:operator must point to idsc:BEFORE and the ids:rightOperand must specify the end timestamp of the interval as xsd:dateTimeStamp."@en ;
.


shapes:IntervalUsageRequestTemplate-permissionPropertyShape
    a sh:PropertyShape ;
    sh:path ids:permission ;
    sh:class ids:Permission ;
    sh:node shapes:IntervalUsageRequestPermissionTemplateShape ;
    sh:minCount 1 ;
    sh:maxCount 1 ;
    sh:severity sh:Violation ;
    sh:message "<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/International-Data-Spaces-Association/InformationModel/master/examples/contract-and-usage-policy/templates/TimeRestrictedUsageTemplates/IntervalUsageRequestTemplateShape.ttl> (IntervalUsageRequestTemplateShape-permissionPropertyShape): In a _:IntervalUsageRequest the ids:permission property must point to at exactly one ids:Permission. In the ids:Permission the ids:target and ids:action properties and at least one of (ids:assigner or ids:assignee) pointing to a participant have to be specified. There must be two ids:constraint properties pointing to an ids:Constraint each. Within one ids:Constrint the ids:leftOperand must point to idsc:POLICY_EVALUATION_TIME, the ids:operator must point to idsc:AFTER and the ids:rightOperand must specify the start timestamp of the interval as xsd:dateTimeStamp. Within the other ids:Constraint the ids:leftOperand must point to idsc:POLICY_EVALUATION_TIME, the ids:operator must point to idsc:BEFORE and the ids:rightOperand must specify the end timestamp of the interval as xsd:dateTimeStamp."@en ;
.


shapes:IntervalUsageRequestPermissionTemplateShape
    a sh:NodeShape ;
    sh:node shapes:HasAssignerOrAssigneeNodeShape ;
    sh:property shapes:PermissionTemplate-targetPropertyShape ;
    sh:property shapes:PermissionTemplate-actionPropertyShape ;
    sh:property shapes:IntervalUsagePermissionTemplate-constraintPropertyShape ;
    sh:property shapes:IntervalUsagePermissionTemplate-constraintPropertyForAfterShape ;
    sh:property shapes:IntervalUsagePermissionTemplate-constraintPropertyForBeforeShape ;
.
